projects.description:
Complex issues and challenges in cities worldwide demand innovative revenue models. One needs to be creative in building a business case in tackling these challenges across varying sectors (e.g. architecture, urban planning, energy, sanitation and mobility).

Under the guidance of several experts (including Oxfam & Plan Nederland) this business case study provided and explored different approaches with other entrepreneurs and urban experts on business modelling to address the issues of accessibility of water & sanitation for lower income groups & cooperation with the informal, private & public sector in Kisumu - Kenya.

· The business case is about an integrated, sustainable approach to urban issues; 
· Inclusion of smaller companies; 
· Provides insights and lessons that are also of value in a different environment or context and are scalable to other cities.
